Somali President Hassan Sheikh Mohamud and Prime Minister Hamza Barre have arrived in the city of Lasanod, the capital of the newly created Northeast State.

This is the first time a Somali president is visiting the region in four decades. The visit coincides with the inauguration of Abdikadir Ahmed Aw-Ali, known as Firdhiye, who was elected in August 2025 as the first president of Somalia’s Northeast State.

They are due to attend the swearing-in ceremony and a series of consultations with traditional elders, civil society leaders, and local officials.

The visit comes at a crucial time as Somalia makes efforts to assert its sovereignty and territorial integrity following recent unilateral recognition of the breakaway region of Somaliland by Israel, which has angered the international community, with many saying Tel Aviv's decision violated Somalia's sovereignty
